        <div class="item">
            <p>
                1. Check-In/Check-Out Procedures:
                Students must adhere to designated check-in and check-out times.
                Proper documentation and permission may be required for overnight stays outside the hostel.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                2. Visitor Policies:

                Guests may be allowed only during specified hours.
                Visitors may need to sign in at the hostel entrance and provide identification.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>3. Quiet Hours:

                Designated quiet hours may be enforced to ensure a conducive study environment.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                4. Room Inspection:

                Hostel staff may conduct periodic room inspections for cleanliness, safety, and adherence to rules.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                5. Curfew:

                A curfew may be imposed, especially for female students, to ensure safety and security.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                6. Anti-Ragging Policies:

                Strict rules against ragging or bullying are typically in place to create a safe environment for all
                residents.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                7. Alcohol and Substance Use:

                Consumption of alcohol or illegal substances may be strictly prohibited.
                Possession of drug paraphernalia may result in disciplinary action.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                8. Smoking Policies:

                Smoking may be restricted to designated areas or completely prohibited within hostel premises.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                9. Safety and Security:

                Hostel residents are expected to follow safety protocols and report any security concerns promptly.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                10. Common Area Usage:

                Respectful use of common areas like kitchens, lounges, and study rooms is generally required.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                11. Laundry Facilities:

                Guidelines for using laundry facilities and schedules may be provided.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                12. Electrical Appliance Usage:

                Restrictions on the use of certain electrical appliances, such as heaters or cooking devices, may be in
                place for safety reasons.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                13. Trash Disposal:

                Residents are typically expected to dispose of their waste responsibly in designated bins.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="item">
            <p>
                14. Gender-Specific Areas:

                Rules may be in place regarding access to gender-specific areas within the hostel.
            </p>
